# Cortex Monolith Overview

This repository is the **modular monolith** (not microservices). Work from the repo root.

## Read first

1. `docs/engineering/README.md`
2. `docs/engineering/how-we-work/feature-placement.md`
3. `docs/engineering/architecture/module-boundaries.md`
4. `AGENTS.md`

Comparison with reference project 2: `docs/engineering/reference/comparison-project-2.md`

## Repo map

```
apps/cortex-server/     → thin FastAPI shell (routers, app.state)
apps/sync-worker/       → Celery -Q sync
apps/ingestion-worker/  → Celery -Q ingestion
apps/web-client/        → React (Vite)
scripts/                → dev.sh, seed-neo4j.sh

packages/module-platform/    → auth, cases, audit, system
packages/module-documents/   → Document CRUD + lifecycle (ONLY status owner)
packages/module-chat/        → Redis threads, chat API
packages/module-sync/        → SyncOrchestrator, job trigger/polling
packages/module-dms-sync/    → DMS delta sync (Celery)
packages/module-ingestion/   → OCR → chunk → embed → Weaviate (case docs, Celery)
packages/module-law-sync/    → Swiss law corpus sync (Celery, -Q sync) — ADR 0009
packages/module-ai/          → LangGraph agents (rag, legal read, nlp)

libs/cortex-core/            → ports, enums, settings, Celery, SearchPort
libs/cortex-models/          → ORM (User, Case, Document, SyncJob, LawVersion, …)
libs/cortex-connectors/      → Alfresco, Blob, OCR, Swiss law source adapters
libs/cortex-observability/   → metrics/tracing hooks
```

## Golden rules

1. **Thin app shell** — no domain logic in `apps/*`, wiring only.
2. **One module = one domain** — do not put features in the wrong module.
3. **Facade pattern** — cross-module calls only via `module_*/api.py`.
4. **ORM only in `cortex-models`** — do not duplicate models in workers.
5. **`Document.status`** — only `DocumentsModule.mark_*()`, never direct ORM writes in workers.
6. **After boundary changes** — run `make lint-imports`.

## Before coding

- New feature → decision table in `feature-placement.mdc`
- HTTP → `schemas/` + `api.py` + `routes/` in the owning module
- Worker → `tasks.py` + `DocumentsModule.mark_*` for status
- Frontend → `apps/web-client/ONBOARDING.md`

## Do not

- Reintroduce `module-alfresco` or `cortex-worker`.
- Add Temporal, CQRS read/write paths, or separate BM25/GDB services.
- Import `module_ai.agents` or `module_*.services` from another module.
- Put law corpus sync in `module-ai` or `module-ingestion` (use `module-law-sync`).
- Add business logic to `cortex-server/main.py`.

